HEADWORD: Trichomatose
<hw>Tri*chom"a*tose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/,
<?/, a growth of hair.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Affected with a
disease which causes agglutination and matting together; -- said of the
hair when affected with plica. See <er>Plica</er>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

